
                                            Toweel died at his home at the age of 83.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - Condolences are pouring in for boxing legend Willie Toweel, who died on Christmas night. Toweel died at his home at the age of 83. He was born in Benoni and comes from a boxing family that included his father Mike. One of his trainees, Brian Mitchell says that Toweel helped him win his South African boxing title in the 1980s. "Willie Toweel was my trainer and manager for many years and made me a South African champion and he will be sorely missed in boxing. He's been out of the fight game for quite a while but the name Willie Toweel will always be remembered in professional boxing."